- Dictates via speech-to-text — expect transcription artifacts, occasional word substitution errors (e.g. "Steven" instead of "Stephen").
- Iterates heavily on individual lines/phrases before moving on.
- Hands hurt with extended typing — minimize burden to retype, post full current state plainly when asked, no extra commentary.
